From df9b5b37eefc8d6318f172307a12e14b2f01bb4f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 11:16:29 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k:WAR: change warn print to peer dbg print

During OTA KPI measurement, a "peer id not found" call trace was observed
while updating user stats from the monitor ring. This issue was not seen
in cabled setups, indicating that the received peer id may not be
associated peer. Fix this by replacing the trace with a peer debug print.

Patch dependency: 0113-0007-wifi-ath12k-Refactor-data-path-pdev-struct.patch

Signed-off-by: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
index b550f3b..5a55e61 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
@@ -1105,8 +1105,8 @@ ath12k_dp_mon_rx_update_user_stats(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *pdev_dp,
 
 	peer = ath12k_dp_link_peer_find_by_ast(dp, user_stats->ast_index);
 	if (!peer) {
-		ath12k_warn(ab, "peer with peer id %d can't be found\n",
-			    ppdu_info->peer_id);
+		ath12k_dbg(ab, ATH12K_DBG_DP_MON_RX, "peer with peer id %d can't be found\n",
+			   ppdu_info->peer_id);
 		return;
 	}
 
-- 
